pullRequest.body:
Cases generated by `fin_cases` are now named according to the order in which they are generated.
For example consider:
```lean
import Mathlib.Tactic

example (x y:Fin 3): (x:‚Ñù)+y < 10 := by
  fin_cases x, y <;> norm_num
``` 
Previously, the case corresponding where `x=1, y=2` would have been displayed as `case tail.head.tail.tail.head`,
where it is now displayed as `case 1.2`

If `fin_cases` is used to replace a goal with an existing name, the existing name will appear in the beginning, for example `goalname.1.2` etc.

Could you add a test showing that the cases are named? You could use something like `#guard_msgs in example ... some setup ... fin_cases ... trace_state`.

Like this?
```lean
/--
info: case 0.0
‚ä¢ True

case 0.1
‚ä¢ True

case 1.0
‚ä¢ True

case 1.1
‚ä¢ True

  fin_cases x, y
  trace_state
  all_goals simp
```

Yes, exactly.

Can you check whether you can select these cases by name too? Like `case 0.0 => ...`? If not, we should use `Name.str` instead of `Name.num`. The `Name.num` is for internal names, so I suspect this case selection won't work.
Good point. Changed to `.str`, so that case names now appear as `case ¬´0¬ª.¬´1¬ª` and `case ¬´0¬ª.¬´1¬ª => ...` works
